WEBVTT

00:09.302 --> 00:11.054
[SCREAMING]

00:12.973 --> 00:15.684
Remember, the safety of the citizens
above all else.

00:16.226 --> 00:19.562
Even your own. We know.
No worries, Batman.

00:19.771 --> 00:24.234
No bystanders will get bashed
with the Outsiders on the job.

00:26.778 --> 00:27.821
[GRUNTING]

00:39.332 --> 00:42.877
Metamorpho, you have to keep
collateral damage to a minimum.

00:44.963 --> 00:46.381
Sari')!-

00:52.262 --> 00:55.223
Contain Despero without destroying
the city in the process.

00:55.432 --> 00:57.434
[BASHING]

01:01.896 --> 01:04.816
Katana, what are you doing?
You're not listening.

01:06.568 --> 01:08.153
[GRUNTS]

01:16.536 --> 01:18.329
BLACK LIGHTNING:
Pretty fast for a big guy...

01:18.538 --> 01:22.876
...but if you wanna beat the Outsiders,
you've gotta be lightning fast.

01:30.008 --> 01:33.470
Katana, Black Lightning,
you're making rookie mistakes.

01:33.678 --> 01:36.639
Are you kidding?
We've got this purple punk on the ropes.

01:41.686 --> 01:43.104
Hopefully.

01:43.313 --> 01:46.941
Remember, strategy and teamwork.
Now take him down.

02:28.775 --> 02:31.820
Ha! That was almost too easy.

02:37.450 --> 02:41.496
- Are you gonna make us clean it up?
BATMAN: No.

02:47.585 --> 02:52.006
You're going to keep doing it
until you get it right.

02:53.967 --> 02:58.763
COMPUTER: Initiate training sequence
Alpha Bar, take 24.

03:02.225 --> 03:03.935
[sun-nus]

04:03.995 --> 04:06.789
[MUSIC PLAYING
<i>&</i> PEOPLE CHATTERING]

04:24.474 --> 04:26.309
Didn't ask you to sit.

04:27.685 --> 04:29.562
That's because
you ain't got no manners.

04:31.689 --> 04:33.816
Son, if you had manners...

04:34.025 --> 04:36.903
...you'd have covered up
that awful mess of a face you got...

04:37.111 --> 04:39.155
...before strutting in here.

04:39.364 --> 04:42.116
[LAUGHING]

04:44.327 --> 04:46.496
I don't think it's nice,
you laughing, Arges.

04:47.705 --> 04:49.415
How do you know my name?

04:53.419 --> 04:57.006
Your name's on my list.
And you probably know mine too.

04:57.799 --> 04:59.550
It's Hex.

05:03.263 --> 05:05.265
Jonah Hex.

05:05.515 --> 05:08.935
Well, I know when I'm outgunned.

05:10.979 --> 05:15.525
But it seems you don't know
when you've been outsmarted.

05:18.111 --> 05:19.821
[GRUNTS]

05:22.573 --> 05:25.785
Lowlife bounty hunters ain't welcome
in this town.

05:26.703 --> 05:30.123
And I aim to make an example
out of you.

05:32.166 --> 05:33.584
<i>[WHISTLES]</i>

05:42.093 --> 05:46.222
Let's see if we can't get you
some scars of your own.

05:46.431 --> 05:49.809
Hex to Warworld, ready for transport.

06:02.155 --> 06:05.867
MONGUL: Again, Jonah Hex lives up
to his timeless reputation.

06:06.117 --> 06:09.996
The greatest bounty hunter
of the millennia.

06:10.455 --> 06:13.750
I don't need flattery from a two-bit,
bushwhacker like you, Mongul.

06:14.000 --> 06:16.753
I'm sick of rounding up roughnecks
for your entertainment.

06:16.961 --> 06:20.089
Entertainment?
My family created Warworld...

06:20.340 --> 06:24.344
...and here, fights are more
than just entertainment.

06:24.594 --> 06:26.095
They are life.

06:26.304 --> 06:28.765
Now, I made good on my word
to bring you fighters.

06:28.973 --> 06:32.352
It's time for you to keep yours
and send me back to my time.

06:33.186 --> 06:36.981
You're right. But first, one more job.

06:37.190 --> 06:40.193
My sister's gladiators
have been dominating the games.

06:40.443 --> 06:45.323
And there's a warrior who might shift
the odds back in my favor.

06:55.666 --> 06:58.628
Two days ago, Zebra-Man,
you told the parole officer...

06:58.836 --> 07:01.422
...you would never use magnetic powers
for evil again.

07:06.177 --> 07:07.595
[GRUNTING]

07:12.183 --> 07:15.395
Looks like you'll never change
your stripes.

07:15.853 --> 07:20.483
Desperate times will twist a man in ways
he never thought he'd bend.

07:20.691 --> 07:22.819
Hex? What are you doing
in the future?

07:23.820 --> 07:26.531
Just trying to make it back
to the past.

07:26.739 --> 07:28.116
Warworld.

07:28.741 --> 07:30.827
This ain't personal.

07:31.035 --> 07:33.371
Now, I always took you
for a civilized fella.

07:33.579 --> 07:36.541
Except for that goofy getup
you parade around in.

07:36.749 --> 07:40.670
So I expect you'll come along
without stirring up a fuss.

07:41.546 --> 07:43.923
Don't mistake my patience
for compliance, Hex.

07:44.173 --> 07:46.092
If you're trying to do this
the hard way...

07:46.300 --> 07:49.429
...you'd better have something better
on the draw than boomerangs.

08:07.405 --> 08:09.991
What does Mongul have on you, Hex?

08:10.241 --> 08:11.576
Saved my hide.

08:11.784 --> 08:14.078
Except, in doing it,
he yanked me to the future.

08:14.287 --> 08:16.747
He ain't gonna send me back
till I repay my debt.

08:27.633 --> 08:30.219
[GRUNTS]

08:33.431 --> 08:37.268
And I aim to repay my debt.

08:49.530 --> 08:52.116
A Gordanian or space pirate
is one thing...

08:52.575 --> 08:55.620
...but capturing the legendary Batman?

08:55.870 --> 08:58.289
Outstanding work, Jonah.

08:58.539 --> 09:02.335
I did just like I said I would.
Now make good on your promise.

09:03.336 --> 09:07.632
I'm afraid not.
You are far too valuable an asset.

09:10.760 --> 09:14.305
Shoot me
and you'll be trapped here forever.

09:14.514 --> 09:17.225
At least I'll have something
to smile about.

09:17.433 --> 09:21.229
MONGAL: Ah-ah-ah!
I wouldn't. My brother may be scum...

09:21.437 --> 09:24.815
...but without him, I'd have no one
to humiliate in the games.

09:25.024 --> 09:30.780
So I must ask you to stand down
or feel the wrath of my Furies.

09:33.032 --> 09:37.203
Come on, cowboy.
I wouldn't mind a crack at you.

09:40.831 --> 09:42.792
Another time, perhaps.

09:44.252 --> 09:46.045
I like big guys like you, Mongul...

09:46.254 --> 09:49.757
"because when you fall,
you make a real big racket.

09:50.007 --> 09:52.051
And you will fall.

09:52.260 --> 09:54.845
That's my word.

09:56.806 --> 09:58.516
Ma am!

10:04.564 --> 10:06.399
MONGAL:
His reputation is certainly great...

10:06.607 --> 10:11.487
...but how long will he last against
my undefeated champion, Steppenwolf?

10:11.696 --> 10:14.198
Let's find out.

10:16.576 --> 10:18.411
[CROWD CHEERING]

10:23.624 --> 10:25.418
From your planet's throne...

10:25.626 --> 10:29.964
...I welcome you to the game
with one winner and no rules:

10:30.172 --> 10:33.092
Battle Arena Warworld.

10:37.263 --> 10:41.142
Steppenwolf is about to do
terrible things to us.

10:41.350 --> 10:45.646
Listen, strength comes in numbers.
We can survive this if we work together.

10:45.855 --> 10:49.734
Yeah? A guy in the last battle
said the same thing.

10:49.942 --> 10:53.571
- How'd that work out for him?
- Ask him yourself.

10:55.990 --> 10:57.158
Right.

10:57.366 --> 11:01.329
Ladies and gentlemen,
the people's champion:

11:01.537 --> 11:04.123
Steppenwolf.

11:06.208 --> 11:09.170
Hundreds before you have fallen
by my axe.

11:09.378 --> 11:13.090
Which of you will be next to accept
such an honor?

11:20.598 --> 11:22.475
[GRUNTS]

11:28.022 --> 11:32.026
Not a fan of Battle Arena Warworld,
I take it?

11:32.234 --> 11:33.944
Afraid not.

11:34.153 --> 11:36.822
If you watched the battles,
you'd know by now...

11:37.031 --> 11:39.617
...cheating is the only way to win.

11:41.869 --> 11:44.497
Since you've been doing such good work
for Mongul...

11:44.705 --> 11:46.916
...I'd be happy to send you back
to your time...

11:47.166 --> 11:49.502
...simply to put him at a disadvantage.

11:49.710 --> 11:51.671
A map to the time tunnel platform...

11:51.921 --> 11:55.508
...and a transceiver you'll need
to activate it.

11:55.925 --> 11:59.804
How do I know you're not just full
of cowpies like your swindling brother?

12:00.346 --> 12:04.642
Because my motives
are entirely selfish.

12:06.143 --> 12:07.853
Ma am!

12:12.274 --> 12:14.151
[GRUNTING]

12:23.577 --> 12:26.539
If I slow him clown long enough,
can you get a clear shot?

12:26.747 --> 12:30.167
If you can slow him down, yes.

12:31.168 --> 12:34.380
Or at least buy myself enough time
to escape.

12:46.434 --> 12:50.146
Looks like you're about to lose again.

12:51.105 --> 12:53.816
It's not over yet.

12:54.024 --> 12:56.152
I was promised a battle
with warriors...

12:56.360 --> 12:58.654
...and instead,
I find nothing but cowards.

12:58.863 --> 13:00.740
Arrogance will be your undoing.

13:07.663 --> 13:09.415
Now.

13:11.751 --> 13:13.711
I should have seen that one coming.

13:13.961 --> 13:15.880
It's you who has been undone...

13:16.088 --> 13:20.468
...by your faith in your
fellow competitors. Ha-ha-ha-ha!

13:21.135 --> 13:24.096
I don't think it's nice, you laughing.

13:24.513 --> 13:26.724
- What's he doing there?
- What's he doing there?

13:27.308 --> 13:30.227
This Hex character's trouble.

13:30.436 --> 13:32.146
So you're the famed bounty hunter...

13:32.354 --> 13:35.566
...who consistently fails
to bring me worthy opponents?

13:35.775 --> 13:39.862
You will fall as easily as them.

13:46.660 --> 13:48.954
Now that just tears it.

14:01.550 --> 14:05.346
The outcome is always the same
for those who take on Steppenwolf.

14:05.554 --> 14:06.847
Defeat.

14:07.056 --> 14:11.769
Then you're about to be humbled
by the hammers of justice.

14:22.822 --> 14:25.282
There's no way.

14:50.850 --> 14:54.728
Batman 1, Steppenwolf 0.

14:54.937 --> 14:57.815
Well, I'll be, you done did it.

14:58.023 --> 15:01.694
Now, come on,
we got bigger hogs to tie up.

15:06.407 --> 15:09.201
Told you he was tough.

15:10.077 --> 15:12.329
Ahh! Cheater.

15:12.955 --> 15:14.206
[LAUGHS]

15:14.456 --> 15:18.502
You're the cheater for trying
to send Hex away behind my back...

15:18.752 --> 15:22.006
...but I assure you,
whatever foolish reason kept him here...

15:22.214 --> 15:23.883
...has nothing to do with me.

15:26.635 --> 15:28.762
- Where are we headed?
- To free the prisoners.

15:28.971 --> 15:32.057
Then I'm gonna take that time tunnel
back home.

15:39.773 --> 15:42.985
MONGAL: You should have left Warworld
when you had the chance, Hex.

15:43.193 --> 15:47.907
Because now I'll make sure
you'll never leave at all.

15:48.115 --> 15:53.621
Stompa, Lashina,
tear our guests apart.

16:01.086 --> 16:02.796
That one's mine.

16:03.005 --> 16:06.425
Got a thing for guys with scars.

16:17.853 --> 16:19.438
[STOMPA GRUNTING]

16:26.487 --> 16:27.738
[LASHINA GRUNTING]

16:32.660 --> 16:35.955
Ohh. Now things really get interesting.

16:36.205 --> 16:38.457
You gonna shoot
an unarmed opponent?

16:39.959 --> 16:41.502
Fair's fair.

16:41.710 --> 16:48.008
Besides, hand-to-hand combat
is so much more personal.

16:48.550 --> 16:52.137
You can tell a lot about a fella
by the way he fights.

16:54.181 --> 16:56.976
So, what do you know
about this fella?

16:58.936 --> 17:02.648
Give me a few more swings
and maybe I'll tell you.

17:33.178 --> 17:34.304
Hm!

17:35.180 --> 17:36.890
Sari')!-

17:39.226 --> 17:42.479
It's been a while
since I've pulped a human in a fight.

17:44.356 --> 17:46.025
[WHISTLES & NEIGHING]

17:47.359 --> 17:49.361
Calling your horse for a getaway?

17:49.570 --> 17:52.698
You're not going anywhere.

17:52.948 --> 17:54.825
No, we sure ain't.

17:56.493 --> 17:58.871
But you are.

17:59.955 --> 18:02.041
[MONGAL YELLS]

18:04.126 --> 18:06.170
Now let's round up the posse.

18:09.465 --> 18:10.507
MONGAL:
Help!

18:14.303 --> 18:17.848
Mongul! Help!

18:18.057 --> 18:23.062
What's that? I can't hear you
over the galloping. Ha-ha-ha!

18:23.353 --> 18:25.814
They're going to
the containment center.

18:26.065 --> 18:27.024
What?

18:40.454 --> 18:42.873
CREATURE:
It's Batman.

18:43.499 --> 18:45.459
[CHEERING]

18:47.377 --> 18:49.671
- Got yourself quite a reputation.
CREATURE: He's with Hex.

18:49.880 --> 18:51.256
Looks like you do too.

18:52.132 --> 18:54.593
[CHATTERING]

18:57.513 --> 18:59.264
Afraid so.

18:59.473 --> 19:02.101
I know you're all real sore at me
for dragging you here.

19:04.728 --> 19:06.146
But I'm busting y'all out.

19:06.355 --> 19:09.483
And as soon as I do,
I'm gonna find Mongul and--

19:11.568 --> 19:14.488
You have very quickly
become far more trouble...

19:14.696 --> 19:17.491
...than you were ever worth, Jonah.

19:56.947 --> 20:00.701
Go ahead. Face ain't gonna get
much worse than it already is.

20:08.083 --> 20:13.714
Ha-ha-ha! What a fool I was to think
you would be a worthy competitor.

20:15.174 --> 20:19.136
You reckon there's a doodad in your belt
that'll bring down a raging bull like him?

20:20.304 --> 20:22.389
I reckon there is.

20:22.598 --> 20:24.266
Fry the cell block controls...

20:24.516 --> 20:26.685
...and you'll destroy
the time tunnel platform.

20:26.935 --> 20:28.520
Hex will never get home.

20:33.901 --> 20:35.027
Go ahead.

20:55.714 --> 20:58.425
He kidnapped you. Destroy him.

21:00.344 --> 21:02.763
It's you we want.

21:06.058 --> 21:08.018
[MONGAL GRUNTS]

21:24.201 --> 21:26.328
Suppose I won't be needing this
anymore.

21:27.037 --> 21:30.916
Well, partner, time to get you home.

21:34.586 --> 21:36.213
I've done my share of time travel.

21:36.421 --> 21:39.049
If you come with me,
I'm sure I can get you back home.

21:39.424 --> 21:44.388
No. I figure I'll stick around here
for a spell, see what comes of it.

21:44.888 --> 21:46.556
Good luck.

21:47.891 --> 21:50.185
See you when I see you.

22:04.157 --> 22:05.784
